  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Italy Earthquake 2016</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">On 24 th August 2016 a magnitude 6.2 earthquake hit Italy 100km north-east of Rome. Amatrice (population 2 000) is the most severely impacted town. Accumoli (population 700) Norcia (population 4 000) and Pescara del Tronto have also been significantly affected. A 5.5 magnitude aftershock hit the same region an hour after the initial EQ and there have been more than 2500 further aftershocks within a week. There have been 292 confirmed fatalities 400 injured and more than 2500 left homeless. A state of emergency has been declared in the region. The Italian authorities are leading the response with involvement of the Italian RC.</narrative>
  </description>
